ng disaccord with my signature. I repeat that never before has any publication acted with such utter sans-gêne towards me. I cannot believe that you are responsible for this mess. Still I would like to have some explanation from the Times in regard to this cavalier treatment. Incidentally they still owe me a quarter of the fee.

Sincerely yours,





TO: PHILIP RAHV1

CC, 1 p.





802 E. Seneca Street

Ithaca, N.Y.

21 May 1949

